<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 31 at 2:51AM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Dallam
and northeastern Hartley Counties through 315 AM CDT...
At 251 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hartley, or 11 miles south of Dalhart, moving northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Hartley.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
